Data Security: an old field


1990's "information security" born

1999: Schwartau "Time-Based Security"

A basic framework for threat-modeling


%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
%page

So What is it?


Protection needs to last longer than the sum of Detection and Reaction time

Protection is not unlimited, everything ultimately broken

Limits of protection mitigated by:
	how quickly breach are detected
	how fast there is a reaction

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
%page

Protection is all about Time


There is no perfect security
	All bank vaults can ultimately be accessed

All cryptography dies with time
	DES was the standard for everything
	same thing will happen with AES in the future

%font "italic", center
How much time does an adversary
need to compromise the assets?

	
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
%page

A simple example


protection = bank vault

detection = alarm system

reaction = security staff

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
%page

Work it through


The alarm system needs to notify the security staff faster than it takes for the adversary to breach the bank vault.

%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
%page

In the Context of Network Security


protection: firewall

detection: intrusion detection system, exceptions in logs

reaction: the alerts to the IT staff



%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
%page

Into everyday: simplified


laptop into an adversary's hands: security is only as good as protection

detection in the past tense

reaction is pointless

